tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated creatinine, suggesting reduced renal function. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), indicating possible renal impairment and/or urinary tract pathology. Hemoglobin A1c is low, which may reflect anemia or altered red cell turnover rather than glycemic control. No evidence of infection (negative nitrites/leukocytes). Recommend further renal evaluation and clinical correlation for possible nephropathy and underlying causes.
